commit.message: chore(*): release 3.51.0 (#807)

Update the test page for the emscripten build (#806)

This test page seems to be designed around a very old build format. With these changes, it works against the 3.50.3 release zip.

CI doesn't use this file, so the CI failure can be ignored.

fix(init/meta/instance_cache): propagate tags through unfreezingI (#804)

The test file is copied from mathlib3.


depends on: #805

ci: Update emscripten container (#805)

The [previous container](https://hub.docker.com/r/trzeci/emscripten/) says "THIS DOCKER IMAGE IS TO BE DEPRECATED".

The new container appears to be running a newer version of emscripten, meaning we need to:
* Link the `nodefs` library to provide `NODEFS`, as this is [not available by default]((https://emscripten.org/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.html#filesystem-api-filesystems).
* Pass `-sDISABLE_EXCEPTION_CATCHING=0` to the compilation step in addition to the link step. Without this we get an immediate crash.

This also makes a shell script slightly more robust.

This was tested using #806, and verifying that the server complains about a garbage `library/init.lean` if I manually put one there with the `FS` API.

fix(library/tactic/simplify): avoid an expensive copy in simp (#801)

In that context, `auto` is deduced to be `expr_map<simp_result>`, which creates a local copy of the map. However, the call to `find()` below can be made on a `const&`, so the copy is unnecessary.

We've measured this copy to be using ~1% of total runtime.

This is intended as a non-functional change. It was generated by automated tools.

fix(frontends/lean/definition_cmds): export `using_well_founded` AST node (#784)

Turns out that the ast.json export has been broken this whole time in ignoring definitions which use `using_well_founded`. cc: @gebner , can we get a point release out with this bugfix?

chore(library/init/meta/declaration): give explicit names to declaration constructor arguments (#783)


These are useful for documentation and generating recursive definitions.

chore(library/init): convert `/-` comments to `/--` or `/-!` comments (#782)

This isn't exhaustive, but converts the majority.
It also does not check that the comments have reasonable markdown formatting.

fix(frontends/lean/pp): correct binder links (#781)

Previously these used the notation definition (the RHS of the `:=`) rather than the matched expression. This usually doesn't work at all, since often the RHS is just `#0` and all the notation happens within the `scoped` block.

This affected a lot of mathlib notation; `Exists`/`infi`/`supr`/`filter.eventually`/`filter.frequently`/...

I don't know if this used to work and then we broke it, or if it's always been broken.
chore(*): release 3.49.0 (#780)

chore(init/core): remove combinator.{I,K,S} (#775)

This is a dead end that should never have been in core. Even now I think these definitions aren't used in mathlib at all. `combinator.K` did get one use in constructing constant closures, used by `exceptional.exception`, but `function.const` is a drop-in replacement that is already used for other things.

feat: extend `pp.links` to support Pi, Prop, Type, and Sort (#778)

This uses `U+E003` (the next available private use character after the ones claimed in #89) to prefix the names:

* `pi`
* `forall`
* `function`
* `implies`
* `Sort`
* `Prop`
* `Type`

The motivation is to be able to link these ideas in doc-gen.
